that, a target for ...c5 and ...e5 counters. But how do we respond when White
holds back on an early d4? We examine this question in this chapter. The lines
tend to be quite harmless for our side, with the possible exception of the
position:} 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. d3 c6 6. Nge2 {. This position may be a bit of
